1
00:01:31,110 --> 00:01:34,740
<b><i>The qualifying round of the second
Divine Visionary Candidate Exam.</i></b>

2
00:01:35,360 --> 00:01:38,240
<b>It is known as "Deadervant's Haunt."</b>

3
00:01:38,950 --> 00:01:43,120
<b><i>A key is hidden inside a Troll-goosefish
swim bladder somewhere in the stage.</i></b>

4
00:01:43,120 --> 00:01:47,580
<b><i>You need to escape by using magic
to pop it like a balloon and obtain the key.</i></b>

5
00:01:48,370 --> 00:01:53,750
<b><i>However, you need to do so
while fleeing from three Deadervants.</i></b>

6
00:01:53,750 --> 00:01:56,510
<b>WAIL</b>

7
00:01:54,000 --> 00:01:56,510
<b>This is impossible!</b>

8
00:01:57,220 --> 00:02:00,510
<b><i>The upcoming qualifying round
is "Deadervant's Haunt."</i></b>

9
00:02:00,800 --> 00:02:04,930
<b><i>Of course, you must pass this
to make it to the main exam!</i></b>

10
00:02:05,770 --> 00:02:09,940
<b><i>Rafflesian Mirrors will transmit
everything to the audience!</i></b>

11
00:02:10,190 --> 00:02:12,310
<b><i>Cheating will not be accepted!</i></b>

12
00:02:12,440 --> 00:02:15,440
<b><i>All entrants, are we ready?</i></b>

13
00:02:18,950 --> 00:02:21,200
<b><i>With that, let the match begin!</i></b>

14
00:02:44,180 --> 00:02:48,850
<b>I want to go home. I just want
to keep sleeping in my bed.</b>

15
00:02:51,650 --> 00:02:54,770
<b>I just gotta find the key, right?</b>

16
00:02:58,150 --> 00:02:58,940
<b>Esepecial!</b>

17
00:03:02,820 --> 00:03:07,540
<b><i>I should mention the Deadervants are
completely immune to magic! So watch out!</i></b>

18
00:03:09,370 --> 00:03:12,580
<b><i>And the moment you touch
one of their axes, it's game over.</i></b>

19
00:03:12,580 --> 00:03:15,630
<b><i>You will be transferred out of the stage
with some soul-splitting pain!</i></b>

20
00:03:19,670 --> 00:03:24,600
<b><i>One has already been disqualified!
We have 11 candidates left!</i></b>

21
00:03:20,470 --> 00:03:24,600
<b>ONE DISQUALIFIED
11 SURVIVORS REMAINING</b>

22
00:03:24,850 --> 00:03:29,680
<b>So I have to keep running from
Deadervants and hunt for the key.</b>

23
00:03:30,060 --> 00:03:32,770
<b>No hints about the key's location, either.</b>

24
00:03:33,270 --> 00:03:38,690
<b>Making us scramble blindly
for a key is a pretty poor test.</b>

25
00:03:39,360 --> 00:03:43,450
<b>Unless there's some
unrevealed strategy going on here.</b>

26
00:03:47,540 --> 00:03:49,620
<b>It is a test after all.</b>

27
00:03:50,120 --> 00:03:54,330
<b>Are they trying to see how we
use our magic to escape the enemy?</b>

28
00:03:54,420 --> 00:03:56,210
<b><i>That's exactly right!</i></b>

29
00:03:56,420 --> 00:03:58,750
<b><i>Deadervants are stand-ins
immune to magic.</i></b>

30
00:03:59,710 --> 00:04:05,640
<b><i>It's limited to this stage, but powerful magic
made them for that purpose.</i></b>

31
00:04:06,220 --> 00:04:10,560
<b><i>When one individual's power
isn't enough to defeat an enemy,</i></b>

32
00:04:10,560 --> 00:04:14,600
<b><i>choosing to retreat
is always a valid tactic.</i></b>

33
00:04:15,270 --> 00:04:21,150
<b><i>This exam questions how well you do
in a situation where you're forced to flee.</i></b>

34
00:04:21,150 --> 00:04:25,660
<b>How tasteless! I knew this school
was messed up, but...</b>

35
00:04:28,660 --> 00:04:31,370
<b>One guy out in the first few moments?</b>

36
00:04:31,580 --> 00:04:34,040
<b>This year's candidates are pretty weak.</b>

37
00:04:34,170 --> 00:04:38,960
<b>Well, last year they had Rayne.
There's no comparing these guys.</b>

38
00:04:39,460 --> 00:04:43,050
<b><i>It's time to run
like your life depends on it!</i></b>

39
00:04:59,020 --> 00:05:01,360
<b>No way! Deadervant down in one hit!?</b>

40
00:05:01,360 --> 00:05:04,070
<b>It's holding its stomach
and breathing heavily.</b>

41
00:05:04,070 --> 00:05:09,780
<b>This test is about how well you do
when you have to retreat, isn't it?</b>

42
00:05:10,410 --> 00:05:13,290
<b>That Deadervant that I couldn't
do anything against...</b>

43
00:05:13,620 --> 00:05:16,710
<b>He's totally nuts!</b>

44
00:05:18,040 --> 00:05:20,500
<b>Now I just need to find the key.</b>

45
00:05:23,380 --> 00:05:27,590
<b><i>That's right. A Deadervant is a phantom.
They are not living creatures.</i></b>

46
00:05:27,890 --> 00:05:31,350
<b><i>Any damage they take
heals instantly, so be careful!</i></b>

47
00:05:31,470 --> 00:05:36,600
<b>BA-DUMP</b>

48
00:05:32,600 --> 00:05:36,600
<b>Oh gosh. Then I won't have anything
to do with them anymore.</b>

49
00:05:36,640 --> 00:05:38,350
<b>DAAAAAAAAAAAASH</b>

50
00:05:38,480 --> 00:05:41,730
<b>So, where is this balloon with the key?</b>

51
00:05:41,980 --> 00:05:42,570
<b>Small.</b>

52
00:05:42,980 --> 00:05:46,110
<b>This is going to be rough
with my puny brain.</b>

53
00:05:47,860 --> 00:05:48,570
<b>Huh?</b>

54
00:05:51,080 --> 00:05:52,870
<b>I've gotten smaller.</b>

55
00:05:53,290 --> 00:05:54,700
<b>I casted a spell.</b>

56
00:05:56,250 --> 00:05:57,210
<b>Over here.</b>

57
00:06:04,170 --> 00:06:05,460
<b>It's gone now.</b>

58
00:06:05,920 --> 00:06:10,220
<b>Deadervants have bad eyesight,
but is really sensitive to sound.</b>

59
00:06:10,550 --> 00:06:12,930
<b>You're fine if you keep that in mind.</b>

60
00:06:13,100 --> 00:06:14,060
<b>Dispel.</b>

61
00:06:18,020 --> 00:06:19,520
<b>I'm back to normal.</b>

62
00:06:20,860 --> 00:06:25,110
<b>My personal magic
changes sizes of things at will.</b>

63
00:06:25,360 --> 00:06:27,780
<b>So that's why I shrunk earlier.</b>

64
00:06:27,780 --> 00:06:28,990
<b>You got it.</b>

65
00:06:29,700 --> 00:06:33,660
<b>Thanks for helping me
even though it's an exam.</b>

66
00:06:33,830 --> 00:06:35,330
<b>Oh, come on now.</b>

67
00:06:35,410 --> 00:06:39,920
<b>It's obvious we'll do better
if we work together.</b>

68
00:06:39,920 --> 00:06:41,290
<b>So it's only natural.</b>

69
00:06:41,630 --> 00:06:45,420
<b>In other words,
we have formed an alliance.</b>

70
00:06:45,670 --> 00:06:47,630
<b>Let's clear the exam together.</b>

71
00:06:47,800 --> 00:06:50,340
<b>Huh? This is too sudden.</b>

72
00:06:51,340 --> 00:06:54,100
<b>Then again, you did save me.</b>

73
00:06:54,350 --> 00:06:56,220
<b>You are too nice.</b>

74
00:06:57,430 --> 00:06:59,480
<b>First, the whereabouts of the key.</b>

75
00:06:59,560 --> 00:07:03,360
<b>I'm certain it's somewhere
in the Deadervant's patrol radius.</b>

76
00:07:03,360 --> 00:07:05,570
<b>Huh? Why is that?</b>

77
00:07:05,770 --> 00:07:07,820
<b>This is an exam after all.</b>

78
00:07:08,150 --> 00:07:11,490
<b>I'm sure they're watching for abilities
in spur-of-the-moment situations as well,</b>

79
00:07:11,490 --> 00:07:16,040
<b>but they should have created the field
so that we can logically deduce an answer.</b>

80
00:07:16,580 --> 00:07:17,450
<b>Huh?</b>

81
00:07:17,790 --> 00:07:19,540
<b>No way, did you pass out?</b>

82
00:07:21,290 --> 00:07:24,500
<b>I'm sorry.
It was a bit hard to understand.</b>

83
00:07:25,170 --> 00:07:26,670
<b>Well, in other words...</b>

84
00:07:26,800 --> 00:07:29,170
<b>BAM</b>

85
00:07:27,710 --> 00:07:29,170
<b>We're going to follow Deadervants.</b>

86
00:07:29,300 --> 00:07:31,630
<b>BOOM</b>

87
00:07:30,340 --> 00:07:31,380
<b>Roger.</b>

88
00:07:33,140 --> 00:07:36,140
<b>SHAKE SHAKE SHAKE SHAKE</b>

89
00:07:36,390 --> 00:07:38,850
<b>Where the hell is this key?</b>

90
00:07:39,020 --> 00:07:41,020
<b>Where is it!</b>

91
00:07:45,190 --> 00:07:46,440
<b>Can this be...</b>

92
00:07:52,070 --> 00:07:55,160
<b>TIP TIP</b>

93
00:07:57,790 --> 00:07:59,620
<b>DON'T MAKE A SOUND.</b>

94
00:07:58,620 --> 00:07:59,620
<b>ROGER.</b>

95
00:08:10,880 --> 00:08:14,260
<b>WE'RE SAFE.</b>

96
00:08:11,170 --> 00:08:13,510
<b>SAFE.</b>

97
00:08:14,970 --> 00:08:16,890
<b>HEY, THAT THING...</b>

98
00:08:21,600 --> 00:08:23,350
<b>I knew it.</b>

99
00:08:24,850 --> 00:08:27,900
<b>The key is in the center of the area
a Deadervant moves around in.</b>

100
00:08:30,730 --> 00:08:34,530
<b>That thing under the balloon... a bellows?</b>

101
00:08:35,030 --> 00:08:37,740
<b>So we inflate it until it bursts? Easy.</b>

102
00:08:37,740 --> 00:08:40,290
<b>Huh? Wait, stop! It's obviously...</b>

103
00:08:40,290 --> 00:08:42,290
<b>HOONK</b>

104
00:08:46,790 --> 00:08:49,130
<b>Are you an idiot?</b>

105
00:08:49,130 --> 00:08:51,340
<b>Now we've done it.</b>

106
00:08:51,590 --> 00:08:53,510
<b>You mean you've done it.</b>

107
00:08:54,300 --> 00:08:55,300
<b>That balloon...</b>

108
00:08:55,550 --> 00:09:01,310
<b>Pressing the bellows to inflate it makes a sound
that calls Deadervants to chase you.</b>

109
00:09:02,180 --> 00:09:05,100
<b>My magic can change the size of objects.</b>

110
00:09:05,270 --> 00:09:08,060
<b>So how do we fill it with air?</b>

111
00:09:09,520 --> 00:09:12,320
<b>Why don't we just break the balloon?</b>

112
00:09:17,410 --> 00:09:21,450
<b>All right, I don't see Deadervants.
Now's the time to rip it up.</b>

113
00:09:21,450 --> 00:09:22,330
<b>'Kay.</b>

114
00:09:22,330 --> 00:09:24,080
<b>HONK</b>

115
00:09:28,040 --> 00:09:31,960
<b>Didn't think touching the balloon
would make a sound, too.</b>

116
00:09:32,050 --> 00:09:33,800
<b>Though, I suppose it would.</b>

117
00:09:34,130 --> 00:09:39,090
<b>That means we can't pull the key
out of the balloon, either.</b>

118
00:09:39,850 --> 00:09:45,100
<b>Perhaps if we break that bellows,
the key just falls out.</b>

119
00:09:47,480 --> 00:09:51,610
<b>The key doesn't fall down,
and the balloon doesn't deflate.</b>

120
00:09:52,110 --> 00:09:55,360
<b>Is the key floating inside by magic?</b>

121
00:09:55,860 --> 00:10:00,530
<b>So we do have to inflate
the balloon with magic.</b>

122
00:10:00,820 --> 00:10:03,740
<b>But what kind of magic?</b>

123
00:10:04,160 --> 00:10:06,120
<b>And we already broke the bellows.</b>

124
00:10:13,960 --> 00:10:15,380
<b>Ready.</b>

125
00:10:17,550 --> 00:10:18,630
<b>Bigduk.</b>

126
00:10:23,720 --> 00:10:28,310
<b>Hey! He just used his magic
to make the balloon bigger.</b>

127
00:10:28,310 --> 00:10:29,980
<b>Is he a moron?</b>

128
00:10:29,980 --> 00:10:32,480
<b>What's he gonna do
by making it harder to burst?</b>

129
00:10:34,110 --> 00:10:37,150
<b><i>By the way, touching the balloon
from the inside also makes a sound,</i></b>

130
00:10:37,280 --> 00:10:39,660
<b><i>so you can't crawl inside, either!</i></b>

131
00:10:40,110 --> 00:10:41,530
<b>Mash.</b>

132
00:10:44,910 --> 00:10:46,660
<b>Huh? What's that?</b>

133
00:10:49,290 --> 00:10:50,920
<b>Is he...</b>

134
00:10:52,380 --> 00:10:54,170
<b>BAM</b>

135
00:10:54,460 --> 00:10:56,670
<b>...about to breakdance!?</b>

136
00:11:00,590 --> 00:11:01,970
<b>Come on, you're joking.</b>

137
00:11:03,100 --> 00:11:04,680
<b>That's impossible!</b>

138
00:11:04,680 --> 00:11:05,850
<b>Seriously impossible.</b>

139
00:11:07,310 --> 00:11:09,060
<b>That's so freaky!</b>

140
00:11:11,600 --> 00:11:13,860
<b><i>The answer is always simple.</i></b>

141
00:11:14,320 --> 00:11:16,690
<b><i>I make the balloon bigger with my magic,</i></b>

142
00:11:16,780 --> 00:11:20,320
<b><i>and we send air into the balloon
through the larger air hole.</i></b>

143
00:11:21,110 --> 00:11:22,530
<b><i>By breakdancing!</i></b>

144
00:11:24,160 --> 00:11:25,200
<b>I see.</b>

145
00:11:25,200 --> 00:11:27,450
<b>M-My hat's off to them.</b>

146
00:11:27,450 --> 00:11:29,210
<b>THROB THROB</b>

147
00:11:38,460 --> 00:11:40,260
<b>A living weapon.</b>

148
00:11:40,470 --> 00:11:42,470
<b>He's a living weapon!</b>

149
00:11:43,640 --> 00:11:44,470
<b>There.</b>

150
00:11:45,010 --> 00:11:47,520
<b>We got the first key!</b>

151
00:11:50,640 --> 00:11:54,980
<b><i>While Mash and Max obtained a key,
in other locations...</i></b>

152
00:11:56,150 --> 00:11:57,230
<b>Graviole.</b>

153
00:12:05,620 --> 00:12:07,620
<b>I guess I pass this round.</b>

154
00:12:20,210 --> 00:12:21,470
<b>Hey.</b>

155
00:12:22,050 --> 00:12:25,890
<b>Don't attack! Don't punch!
I hate pain! I'm sorry!</b>

156
00:12:25,890 --> 00:12:27,720
<b>Are you all right, Finn?</b>

157
00:12:29,060 --> 00:12:30,140
<b>Dot!</b>

158
00:12:30,140 --> 00:12:32,270
<b>You got your key already?</b>

159
00:12:33,440 --> 00:12:37,310
<b>You're so hopeless.
I'll help you out, then.</b>

160
00:12:37,690 --> 00:12:39,150
<b>Dot, you're bleeding!</b>

161
00:12:39,230 --> 00:12:40,990
<b>You're so hopeless.</b>

162
00:12:40,990 --> 00:12:42,190
<b>No, but blood!</b>

163
00:12:42,740 --> 00:12:44,410
<b>You're so hopeless!</b>

164
00:12:44,410 --> 00:12:45,910
<b>I'm telling you, blood!</b>

165
00:12:46,160 --> 00:12:49,030
<b>Hurray, hurray, hurray.</b>

166
00:12:49,450 --> 00:12:51,580
<b>Well, we somehow made it.</b>

167
00:12:51,750 --> 00:12:53,660
<b>For a while, I was wondering
what would happen.</b>

168
00:12:53,660 --> 00:12:55,210
<b>So, um...</b>

169
00:12:55,210 --> 00:12:57,040
<b>Hm? What is it?</b>

170
00:12:57,500 --> 00:12:58,540
<b>Here.</b>

171
00:12:58,750 --> 00:12:59,590
<b>Huh?</b>

172
00:12:59,960 --> 00:13:04,300
<b>We got this key thanks to you,
so please take it.</b>

173
00:13:08,350 --> 00:13:10,760
<b>You really are a good person.</b>

174
00:13:11,100 --> 00:13:13,810
<b>Huh? That's not really true.</b>

175
00:13:14,350 --> 00:13:16,810
<b>You should take that key.</b>

176
00:13:20,150 --> 00:13:21,780
<b>The exit is that way.</b>

177
00:13:22,070 --> 00:13:25,990
<b>There's a rumor that time
is a factor in your ranking.</b>

178
00:13:26,070 --> 00:13:27,870
<b>Huh? But...</b>

179
00:13:28,700 --> 00:13:32,830
<b>Actually, I heard
all about you from Rayne.</b>

180
00:13:33,250 --> 00:13:34,790
<b>Mr. Rabbits.</b>

181
00:13:35,080 --> 00:13:39,080
<b>I really didn't think you were
this good-natured.</b>

182
00:13:39,710 --> 00:13:44,840
<b>I got the gist of how to obtain the key.
I can do the rest by myself.</b>

183
00:13:45,590 --> 00:13:48,800
<b>Mash, I'm just trying to act tough.</b>

184
00:13:49,470 --> 00:13:53,720
<b>It's my ego saying that I want
to do something for people like you.</b>

185
00:13:54,060 --> 00:13:55,390
<b>So don't worry.</b>

186
00:13:59,190 --> 00:14:03,650
<b>It's an important job for a junior
to keep a senior's honor.</b>

187
00:14:04,940 --> 00:14:05,900
<b>'Kay.</b>

188
00:14:10,410 --> 00:14:12,030
<b>Thank you very much.</b>

189
00:14:20,540 --> 00:14:21,880
<b>Now then...</b>

190
00:14:33,310 --> 00:14:35,640
<b>My bad hunch was right.</b>

191
00:14:37,020 --> 00:14:40,480
<b>Carpaccio Luo-yang of Orca.</b>

192
00:14:46,280 --> 00:14:49,780
<b>Was I able to act like a senior, Rayne?</b>

193
00:14:51,160 --> 00:14:52,410
<b>Bring it on.</b>

194
00:14:56,450 --> 00:15:00,960
<b><i>Now, candidates who obtained keys
are filing in one after another!</i></b>

195
00:14:59,750 --> 00:15:02,080
<b>Here are drinks and towels.</b>

196
00:15:11,550 --> 00:15:12,970
<b>Mash!</b>

197
00:15:15,850 --> 00:15:17,640
<b>Dot, Finn.</b>

198
00:15:17,810 --> 00:15:21,980
<b>Balloons and explosive magic
was a good pairing.</b>

199
00:15:21,980 --> 00:15:23,690
<b>That said, you have quite a wound.</b>

200
00:15:23,940 --> 00:15:27,150
<b>I got Finn's key as well.</b>

201
00:15:28,360 --> 00:15:29,700
<b>Are you okay?</b>

202
00:15:31,610 --> 00:15:36,410
<b>I'm surprised you defeated that balloon
without using magic.</b>

203
00:15:36,410 --> 00:15:38,700
<b>Well, I had help so I managed somehow.</b>

204
00:15:39,710 --> 00:15:42,210
<b>But why did he give me the key?</b>

205
00:15:42,960 --> 00:15:45,340
<b>It seems like he had
some reason to do so.</b>

206
00:15:46,380 --> 00:15:47,460
<b>What's wrong?</b>

207
00:15:47,630 --> 00:15:49,380
<b>No, just...</b>

208
00:15:51,050 --> 00:15:53,590
<b><i>Only nine people
can advance to the next stage!</i></b>

209
00:15:53,890 --> 00:15:57,100
<b><i>Who will take that final spot?</i></b>

210
00:16:04,940 --> 00:16:05,980
<b>There he...</b>

211
00:16:09,940 --> 00:16:11,400
<b><i>And there you have it!</i></b>

212
00:16:11,400 --> 00:16:13,240
<b><i>The last one is...</i></b>

213
00:16:13,490 --> 00:16:17,620
<b><i>Orca dorm's Carpaccio Luo-yang!</i></b>

214
00:16:20,330 --> 00:16:24,000
<b><i>But this is quite horrible.
There's so much blood.</i></b>

215
00:16:24,250 --> 00:16:27,420
<b><i>Was there a need to hurt him this badly?</i></b>

216
00:16:27,670 --> 00:16:32,010
<b><i>Could this be a declaration of war!?</i></b>

217
00:16:34,340 --> 00:16:36,140
<b>I don't need weaklings.</b>

218
00:16:36,930 --> 00:16:38,760
<b>Weaklings are useless.</b>

219
00:16:39,720 --> 00:16:44,100
<b>So it shouldn't matter
what I do to them.</b>

220
00:16:44,190 --> 00:16:45,230
<b>Excuse me.</b>

221
00:16:46,360 --> 00:16:48,020
<b>What are you doing?</b>

222
00:16:48,360 --> 00:16:50,610
<b>If you go any further, I'll punch you.</b>

223
00:16:51,070 --> 00:16:54,280
<b>More like, did you really
have to go that far?</b>

224
00:16:54,530 --> 00:16:58,580
<b>I just said it.
I can do whatever I want.</b>

225
00:16:59,080 --> 00:17:03,870
<b><i>Carpaccio Luo-yang.
The top continuing student for this year.</i></b>

226
00:17:04,080 --> 00:17:08,000
<b><i>Just like Lance, he's a true elite.</i></b>

227
00:17:11,510 --> 00:17:13,670
<b>H-Here's your drink and towel.</b>

228
00:17:24,980 --> 00:17:27,690
<b>Weaklings should keep quiet.</b>

229
00:17:27,690 --> 00:17:28,940
<b>SLUP SUP SUP SUP</b>

230
00:17:34,070 --> 00:17:35,700
<b>Can that be...</b>

231
00:17:37,360 --> 00:17:38,530
<b>PHEW</b>

232
00:17:39,070 --> 00:17:44,000
<b>Sorry. It's 3 o'clock, which is when I like
to take my homemade special muscle drink.</b>

233
00:17:44,000 --> 00:17:46,170
<b>It's a protein shake!</b>

234
00:17:46,170 --> 00:17:50,210
<b>Powdered beans.
It makes it easier to absorb protein.</b>

235
00:17:50,420 --> 00:17:55,720
<b><i>The nerve of making a protein shake with
the water that was about to go on his head. Scary.</i></b>

236
00:17:56,090 --> 00:18:00,390
<b>Sorry, but a schedule for protein
consumption is very important.</b>

237
00:18:01,100 --> 00:18:04,560
<b>Also, you keep calling people "weaklings."</b>

238
00:18:04,640 --> 00:18:09,020
<b>But I have yet to meet
anyone stronger than me.</b>

239
00:18:12,400 --> 00:18:16,030
<b>Besides, the definition of strength
differs from person to person.</b>

240
00:18:16,780 --> 00:18:17,740
<b>Wait.</b>

241
00:18:17,820 --> 00:18:23,620
<b>HONK</b>

242
00:18:18,740 --> 00:18:20,870
<b>What does it mean to be strong?</b>

243
00:18:20,870 --> 00:18:23,620
<b>He brought up the topic,
but he confused himself.</b>

244
00:18:35,090 --> 00:18:36,670
<b><i>Hold it right there!</i></b>

245
00:18:37,300 --> 00:18:39,840
<b><i>Save the fighting for the examination!</i></b>

246
00:18:40,140 --> 00:18:41,760
<b><i>Is that understood!?</i></b>

247
00:18:41,970 --> 00:18:45,060
<b><i>Without further ado,
let's move on to the next exam!</i></b>

248
00:18:56,190 --> 00:18:58,200
<b>Our robes changed colors?</b>

249
00:18:59,160 --> 00:19:01,490
<b><i>Here's your next exam!</i></b>

250
00:19:02,490 --> 00:19:05,160
<b><i>It's called "The Life Crystal."</i></b>

251
00:19:06,700 --> 00:19:08,460
<b><i>This will be a team battle!</i></b>

252
00:19:08,710 --> 00:19:10,250
<b><i>Each team has three members.</i></b>

253
00:19:10,250 --> 00:19:13,420
<b><i>With nine candidates,
we will have three teams!</i></b>

254
00:19:13,670 --> 00:19:17,840
<b><i>After the teams are set, the three members
will get one crystal each.</i></b>

255
00:19:17,970 --> 00:19:21,260
<b><i>And you will go break the crystals
of opposing teams!</i></b>

256
00:19:21,430 --> 00:19:24,850
<b><i>A team is disqualified
when all their crystals are broken!</i></b>

257
00:19:25,010 --> 00:19:26,560
<b>I see.</b>

258
00:19:26,560 --> 00:19:28,680
<b>So that's why it's a team match.</b>

259
00:19:33,190 --> 00:19:38,110
<b>Yo! Your explanation's too complicated
and our captain's brain isn't keeping up!</b>

260
00:19:38,110 --> 00:19:40,820
<b>Make it easier to understand, damn it!</b>

261
00:19:40,820 --> 00:19:46,450
<b><i>W-Well, in other words, you split up
into teams and break each other's crystals.</i></b>

262
00:19:46,620 --> 00:19:50,620
<b>So we just smash everyone
else's crystals. That's easy!</b>

263
00:19:50,710 --> 00:19:54,750
<b>Mash, smash crystal. Mash, smash crystal.</b>

264
00:19:54,920 --> 00:19:56,880
<b>That's right! Smash! Smash 'em!</b>

265
00:19:56,880 --> 00:19:59,550
<b>Smash crystal.</b>

266
00:19:59,550 --> 00:20:00,760
<b><i>Moreover...</i></b>

267
00:20:01,340 --> 00:20:05,050
<b><i>Lance is in a different team.
What should we do?</i></b>

268
00:20:06,640 --> 00:20:08,890
<b><i>Now we will hand out the crystals.</i></b>

269
00:20:11,690 --> 00:20:15,270
<b><i>These crystals are fragile,
so handle them carefully!</i></b>

270
00:20:17,320 --> 00:20:22,360
<b>These crystals determine the exam results,
and therefore our fate.</b>

271
00:20:23,240 --> 00:20:28,160
<b><i>Each team has three members.
If all our crystals break, we drop out.</i></b>

272
00:20:28,160 --> 00:20:29,830
<b><i>So even if mine breaks, at least...</i></b>

273
00:20:34,500 --> 00:20:35,460
<b>It slipped.</b>

274
00:20:37,630 --> 00:20:41,220
<b><i>W-We're still fine. Dot's crystal...</i></b>

275
00:20:45,930 --> 00:20:48,100
<b>This thing was so slippery.</b>

276
00:20:50,520 --> 00:20:55,190
<b>GLOOM</b>

277
00:20:50,980 --> 00:20:55,190
<b>HEART TEAM'S (TWO) CRYSTALS</b>

278
00:20:51,980 --> 00:20:55,190
<b>LIFESPAN</b>

279
00:20:52,940 --> 00:20:55,190
<b>23 SECONDS</b>

280
00:20:55,190 --> 00:20:56,900
<b>Bad, bad, very bad!</b>

281
00:20:56,900 --> 00:20:59,650
<b>This means that it's all over
if my crystal breaks.</b>

282
00:20:59,650 --> 00:21:01,440
<b>Oh, don't worry.</b>

283
00:21:02,530 --> 00:21:06,370
<b>We'll make sure to protect
your crystal through all of this.</b>

284
00:21:07,490 --> 00:21:08,990
<b>You guys.</b>

285
00:21:09,490 --> 00:21:12,500
<b><i>That's right. As long as
these two are at my side.</i></b>

286
00:21:14,170 --> 00:21:18,210
<b><i>Wait, why are you looking so smug?
You should show some remorse.</i></b>

287
00:21:18,210 --> 00:21:20,460
<b><i>Everyone, sorry for the wait!</i></b>

288
00:21:20,550 --> 00:21:22,880
<b><i>Time to begin the exam!</i></b>

289
00:21:22,970 --> 00:21:24,840
<b><i>Stage shift!</i></b>

290
00:21:37,150 --> 00:21:41,610
<b><i>Just like the previous round, candidates
will be scattered throughout the stage!</i></b>

291
00:21:41,860 --> 00:21:49,620
<b><i>Which team will protect their crystals
to the end and pass this exam!?</i></b>

292
00:21:49,620 --> 00:21:52,120
<b>ALONE...</b>

293
00:21:52,580 --> 00:21:57,710
<b>I-It's a team match,
so why are we forced to split apart!?</b>

294
00:21:58,290 --> 00:21:59,880
<b>Damn it!</b>

295
00:22:01,500 --> 00:22:03,260
<b><i>He was all alone.</i></b>

296
00:23:35,220 --> 00:23:39,940
<b>NEXT EPISODE
FINN AMES AND THE FRIEND</b>

